<title>POLAND: KPW clears LDA new issue.</title>
<headline>KPW clears LDA new issue.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1997-08-14</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Polish Securities Commission (KPW) has cleared for public trade the new issue of 2.9 million shares of printing firm Lodzka Drukarnia Akcydensowa SA (LDA), the KPW said in a statement on Thursday.</p>
<p> Tranches		     No Of Shares	   Subscription</p>
<p>				  Offered		  Period</p>
<p> Common shrs series C*    650,000-1,383,440    Sep 22-Aug 13</p>
<p> Registered shrs series C** 271,530		Nov 3-17</p>
<p> Common shrs series D***  1,250,000		Sep 22-Oct 3</p>
<p>Note: * Shares for current shareholders who purchased shares by September 15. ** Shares for series A registered shareholders. *** Shares for owners of cenvertible bonds, conversion to take place between August 14, 1997 and August 11, 2000.</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
